WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.234 --> 00:00:04.804 align:start position:0% line:91%
&gt;&gt;  THE WINTER OF
2015 HAS WREAKED HAVOC ALL OVER

00:00:04.837 --> 00:00:07.573 line:91%
THE NORTHEAST, AND SOME NEW
YORKERS HAVE SEEN THEIR HOMES

00:00:07.606 --> 00:00:09.675 align:start position:0% line:91%
DESTROYED BY THE RECENT
BLIZZARD.

00:00:09.708 --> 00:00:14.113 line:85%
STATEN ISLANDERS AIMAN YOUSSEF.

00:00:14.146 --> 00:00:15.048 align:start position:0% line:85%
&gt;&gt; IT WAS NOT BLIZZARD.

00:00:15.081 --> 00:00:16.082 align:start position:0% line:85%
&gt;&gt; RIGHT. AN ICE STORM.

00:00:16.115 --> 00:00:17.050 size:84% position:42% line:85%
&gt;&gt; IT WAS NOT AN ICE STORM.

00:00:17.083 --> 00:00:18.084 align:start position:0% line:85%
&gt;&gt; FROZEN HAIL?

00:00:18.117 --> 00:00:19.585 size:78% position:39% line:85%
&gt;&gt; THAT'S NOT IT, EITHER.

00:00:19.618 --> 00:00:21.821 size:88% position:44% line:85%
IT WAS FROM HURRICANE SANDY.

00:00:21.854 --> 00:00:24.057 align:start position:0% line:91%
&gt;&gt; WHAT, THAT WAS LIKE TWO YEARS
AGO.

00:00:24.090 --> 00:00:25.892 align:start position:0% line:91%
&gt;&gt; EXACTLY, TWO YEARS AGO, WE'RE
STILL IN A TENT.

00:00:25.925 --> 00:00:26.492 align:start position:0% line:85%
&gt;&gt; WHAT?

00:00:26.526 --> 00:00:28.561 size:78% position:39% line:85%
WE HAD A CONCERT TO HELP.

00:00:28.594 --> 00:00:32.498 line:91%
WE HAD MICK JAGGER THERE AND THE
BOSS WAS THERE AND THEN WE HAD

00:00:32.531 --> 00:00:35.034 align:start position:0% line:91%
ANOTHER CONCERT AND THERE WERE
COMMERCIALS AND THIS GUY IS

00:00:35.067 --> 00:00:36.269 align:start position:0% line:85%
STILL IN A TENT?

00:00:36.302 --> 00:00:37.970 align:start position:0% line:91%
SO THIS IS WHERE YOUR HOUSE USED
TO BE.

00:00:38.003 --> 00:00:38.771 align:start position:0% line:85%
&gt;&gt; CORRECT.

00:00:38.804 --> 00:00:40.139 align:start position:0% line:91%
&gt;&gt; THIS USED TO BE YOUR LIVING
ROOM?

00:00:40.172 --> 00:00:40.673 align:start position:0% line:85%
&gt;&gt; YES.

00:00:40.706 --> 00:00:42.175 align:start position:0% line:85%
&gt;&gt; AND HE'S NOT ALONE.

00:00:42.208 --> 00:00:46.179 align:start position:0% line:91%
THERE ARE THOUSANDS OF PEOPLE
STILL WITHOUT HOMES.

00:00:46.212 --> 00:00:47.713 line:85%
&gt;&gt; NOBODY'S HOME, ME INCLUDED.

00:00:47.746 --> 00:00:49.816 align:start position:0% line:91%
&gt;&gt; IT'S BEEN ALMOST TWO AND A
HALF YEARS ALREADY.

00:00:49.849 --> 00:00:50.683 size:88% position:44% line:85%
IT SHOULD HAVE BEEN REBUILT.

00:00:50.716 --> 00:00:52.919 align:start position:0% line:91%
&gt;&gt; YOU KNOW, WE'RE FROM NEW
YORK.

00:00:52.952 --> 00:00:54.454 align:start position:0% line:91%
HOW COULD THIS POSSIBLY TAKE
THIS LONG?

00:00:54.487 --> 00:01:00.660 line:91%
&gt;&gt; OKAY, WAIT, MORE THAN $648
MILLION WAS SET ASIDE FOR AN

00:01:00.693 --> 00:01:03.663 line:91%
ORGANIZATION CALLED BUILD IT
BACK WHICH WAS CREATED SOLELY

00:01:03.696 --> 00:01:07.867 align:start position:0% line:91%
TO-- IT'S IN THE NAME-- BUILD
PEOPLE'S HOUSES BACK.

00:01:07.900 --> 00:01:10.002 size:88% position:44% line:85%
WHAT HAPPENED TO THOSE GUYS?

00:01:10.035 --> 00:01:11.270 line:85%
&gt;&gt; BUILD IT BACK REALLY SUCKS.

00:01:11.303 --> 00:01:13.773 align:start position:0% line:91%
&gt;&gt; BUILT IT BACK, THEY BUILD
NOTHING.

00:01:13.806 --> 00:01:15.074 align:start position:0% line:85%
&gt;&gt; THEY LOSE PAPERWORK.

00:01:15.107 --> 00:01:17.577 align:start position:0% line:91%
IT'S JUST BEEN-- NO ANSWERS, AND
NO PROGRESS.

00:01:17.610 --> 00:01:20.880 align:start position:0% line:91%
&gt;&gt; WE HAVE NO HOMES BUT WE PAY
TAXES ON THOSE HOMES.

00:01:20.913 --> 00:01:21.681 align:start position:0% line:91%
&gt;&gt; THAT'S RIGHT.
&gt;&gt; WHAT?

00:01:21.714 --> 00:01:23.649 align:start position:0% line:91%
&gt;&gt; I'M STILL PAYING
FLOOD INSURANCE.

00:01:23.682 --> 00:01:25.818 line:91%
THEY DIDN'T FINISH PAYING ME,
BUT I AM STILL PAYING THEM.

00:01:25.851 --> 00:01:29.122 align:start position:0% line:91%
&gt;&gt; WE NEED TWO FLOORS AND THEY
ONLY WANT TO FINISH ONE.

00:01:29.155 --> 00:01:31.991 align:start position:0% line:91%
AND ALL WE WANT IS WHAT WE HAD
BEFORE.

00:01:32.024 --> 00:01:33.426 align:start size:97% position:3% line:91%
SIMPLE KITCHEN, SIMPLE LIVING
ROOM AND A BATHROOM.

00:01:33.459 --> 00:01:34.560 line:85%
&gt;&gt; WOAH, WOAH, WOAH. WHAT ELSE?

00:01:34.593 --> 00:01:38.197 align:start size:88% position:13% line:91%
&gt;&gt; DOORS WOULD BE NICE. 
&gt;&gt; PLURAL.

00:01:38.230 --> 00:01:39.332 align:start position:0% line:91%
&gt;&gt; YEAH, DOORS ON THE BEDROOMS,
MAYBE A FRONT DOOR.

00:01:39.365 --> 00:01:42.568 align:start position:0% line:91%
&gt;&gt; YOU SEE HOW THIS COULD TAKE A
WHILE.

00:01:42.601 --> 00:01:45.671 align:start position:0% line:91%
IF I DO THE MATH HERE, THIS IS A
17-YEAR PROJECT.

00:01:45.704 --> 00:01:49.442 align:start size:94% position:6% line:91%
